<TITLE> UNDP offers support to HRC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 20 (bdnews24.com)  UNDP on Monday offered support to build up and make effective Bangladesh's nascent Human Rights Commission. The UN Development Programme was also ready to provide financial and technical aid for strengthening the judiciary, resident representative Renata Lok Dessallien told reporters. Dessallien spoke to reporters after a meeting with law minister Shafiq Ahmed on Monday. The law minister said great backlogs of cases are pending now in courts across the country, though no accurate figure is available. He felt the need for an appropriate authority for speedy disposal of cases, he said. On validating the caretaker government's ordinances, the minister said they would approve those related to elections and finance. He also said bills for some other ordinances would be presented before the parliament and decisions would be taken after discussion, the rest would be repealed. bdn
